<br>
What concerns me is the styles that have been made 'good' not being ones we would be using most of the time. This may be all well and good in PvE, where we can organise stuff with a backup tank or something so we get to spam 'Rain, but in RvR, outside of a duel we're going to be using the anytime styles for the greatest part. And MAYBE D-Shadows if we can manage.<br>
<br>
Putting the lovely-sounding (but probably disappointing TBH) bleed of DS aside, we still have the same problem we always had, which is that we can't consistently deal damage that doesn't suck. We're still using 62% (or wahtever) and 79% styles and getting the bonus only on our mainhand, and hitting for 3x with our offhand.<br>
<br>
People love to talk about how great amethyst slash is, but I... don't. The only times I feel like I'm hitting for my weapons worth in gold is when i do a Diamonder on somebody.<br>
<br>
The 'zerkers are complaining now that seeing as they're supposed to be backup tanks they have no decent chains, bleeds, side-styles, y'know, the lovely gimmicks we got. But for the merc (and maybe the BM, though I haven't checked out their style changes and TW sounds fantastic!) our only 'goodened' styles are-<br>
<br>
-Parry reactionary (HypDark stun and 'Tendrils)<br>
-Front-based (DShadows)<br>
-Side-based ('Rain which can only really be pulled off after the stun in RvR)<br>
<br>
Some nice looking damage in those styles, but we still sound like duellists to me, and nothing given to me in this patch will help me hit a healer for any more than I did last time... which &quot;sucked&quot;.<br>
<br>
The few style overhauls they did showed nice willing, but they need to finish. In my eyes, MG is a waste of a style space, our back-chain (something we can possibly actually pull off, sometimes) needs upping in damage and maybe given a hinder <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> a la </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Pole-Arm, and, well, at least they tried with the evade requirement overload we had. I'd love to see Orbit's chain being given a stun for all those dodgers out there and the people who spec sla-, uh, crush.<br>
<br>
But again, that's duellists stuff <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> Would you think a man going naked with a sword is scarier than a man going naked with an axe? </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> - Tatsumaru<br>
